  "prompt": "Is there a 5 star general?",
  "response": "Yes, in the United States military, a \"5-star general\" refers to the rank of General of the Army in the Army and General of the Air Force in the Air Force. This rank is above a 4-star general and is a five-star designation. There have been only a few individuals who have achieved this rank, primarily during World War II. Notable 5-star generals in U.S. history include George Washington (posthumously appointed in 1976), Douglas MacArthur, William D. Leahy, and Omar Bradley. As of now, there are no active 5-star generals in the U.S. military.",
